  "prompt": "What are the Upcoming mobiles?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, I can't provide real-time information or upcoming mobile releases beyond that date. However, major smartphone manufacturers typically have announcements scheduled for certain times of the year. Here are some expected trends and releases based on past patterns:\n\n1. **Apple**: Apple usually announces new iPhone models in September. The next-gen iPhone models are typically anticipated in that timeframe.\n\n2. **Samsung**: Samsung often releases its Galaxy S series in the first half of the year (usually around February or March). The Galaxy Note series has seen less frequent updates lately, but new foldable devices (like the Galaxy Z Fold and Z Flip) are generally unveiled in the summer.\n\n3. **Google**: Google commonly launches its Pixel phones in the fall, typically in October.\n\n4. **OnePlus**: OnePlus usually reveals new models in the first half and later in the second half of the year.\n\n5. **Xiaomi and Realme**: These brands often release new devices throughout the year, including mid-range and flagship smartphones.\n\n6. **Others**: Brands like Oppo, Vivo, and Sony also announce new devices throughout the year, sometimes aligning with major tech shows or their own launch events.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information on upcoming mobile phones, it's best to check tech news websites, manufacturer announcements, or reliable leaks from industry insiders.",
